[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":476},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F24\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-docker-hub\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F24\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-docker-hub\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F24\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-docker-hub\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F24\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-docker-hub\u002F":453,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F24\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-docker-hub\u002F":462},"\u002Fdocker\u002F20230124\u002F1507289668\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":434,"date":435,"description":436,"extension":437,"lang":438,"meta":439,"navigation":440,"path":441,"readingMinutes":442,"seo":443,"standalone":444,"stem":445,"tags":446,"tldr":449,"updated":450,"url":451,"__hash__":452},"content\u002Fen\u002FDocker\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-docker-hub.md","(4) Step-by-Step Docker — Docker Hub","2463750185",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":422},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,47,50,61,70,77,80,83,87,90,143,148,154,159,166,169,267,270,274,280,302,305,309,314,330,333,339,343,346,360,363,368,371,400,403,406,410,415,418],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Next up, let's talk about another important part of Docker — Docker Hub.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"docker-hub","Docker Hub",[17,25,26],{},"Docker maintains a registry platform called Docker Hub. The name \"Hub\" might immediately remind you of GitHub. They do similar-ish things, but with a key difference:",[28,29,30,39],"ul",{},[31,32,33,34],"li",{},"GitHub\n",[28,35,36],{},[31,37,38],{},"A platform for hosting code",[31,40,41,42],{},"Docker Hub\n",[28,43,44],{},[31,45,46],{},"A platform for hosting Docker Images",[17,48,49],{},"So they're related but not the same.",[17,51,52,53,60],{},"Docker Hub has both public and private repositories. The catch is Docker Hub only includes one private repository for free, while public ones are unlimited. If you want more details, check ",[54,55,59],"a",{"href":56,"rel":57},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.docker.com\u002Fpricing\u002F",[58],"nofollow","Docker's pricing page",".",[17,62,63,64,69],{},"If you haven't registered on Docker Hub yet, ",[54,65,68],{"href":66,"rel":67},"https:\u002F\u002Fhub.docker.com\u002Fsignup",[58],"register here",". I won't walk through the signup details — assuming you've registered and logged in, your screen should look something like this:",[17,71,72],{},[73,74],"img",{"alt":75,"src":76},"Docker Hub home","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E4%B8%80%E6%AD%A5%E6%AD%A5%E6%8E%8C%E6%8F%A1%E5%9F%BA%E7%A4%8E-Docker\u002F7rMbxbf.png",[17,78,79],{},"If your screen looks similar, you're logged in.",[17,81,82],{},"(The UI changes between Docker Hub versions, but the concepts are the same.)",[12,84,86],{"id":85},"docker-hub-commands","Docker Hub commands",[17,88,89],{},"Now let's go through the basic Docker Hub commands. The essentials:",[28,91,92,103,113,123,133],{},[31,93,94,98],{},[95,96,97],"code",{},"docker login",[28,99,100],{},[31,101,102],{},"Log in to Docker Hub",[31,104,105,108],{},[95,106,107],{},"docker logout",[28,109,110],{},[31,111,112],{},"Log out of Docker Hub",[31,114,115,118],{},[95,116,117],{},"docker search",[28,119,120],{},[31,121,122],{},"Search for Images on Docker Hub",[31,124,125,128],{},[95,126,127],{},"docker pull",[28,129,130],{},[31,131,132],{},"Pull an Image from Docker Hub",[31,134,135,138],{},[95,136,137],{},"docker push",[28,139,140],{},[31,141,142],{},"Push an Image to Docker Hub",[144,145,147],"h3",{"id":146},"logging-in-to-docker-hub","Logging in to Docker Hub",[17,149,150,151,153],{},"In your terminal, run ",[95,152,97],{},". It'll ask for your Docker Hub username and password.",[17,155,156],{},[73,157],{"alt":97,"src":158},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E4%B8%80%E6%AD%A5%E6%AD%A5%E6%8E%8C%E6%8F%A1%E5%9F%BA%E7%A4%8E-Docker\u002FeZS3Wzo.png",[17,160,161,162,165],{},"(If you see ",[95,163,164],{},"Error response from daemon: Get \"https:\u002F\u002Fregistry-1.docker.io\u002Fv2\u002F\": unauthorized: incorrect username or password",", your credentials are wrong.)",[17,167,168],{},"On success you'll see:",[170,171,176],"pre",{"className":172,"code":173,"language":174,"meta":175,"style":175},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","Logging in with your password grants your terminal complete access to your account.\nFor better security, log in with a limited-privilege personal access token. Learn more at https:\u002F\u002Fdocs.docker.com\u002Fgo\u002Faccess-tokens\u002F\n","bash","",[95,177,178,222],{"__ignoreMap":175},[179,180,183,187,191,194,197,200,203,205,208,211,214,217,219],"span",{"class":181,"line":182},"line",1,[179,184,186],{"class":185},"smYoP","Logging",[179,188,190],{"class":189},"sWayO"," in",[179,192,193],{"class":189}," with",[179,195,196],{"class":189}," your",[179,198,199],{"class":189}," password",[179,201,202],{"class":189}," grants",[179,204,196],{"class":189},[179,206,207],{"class":189}," terminal",[179,209,210],{"class":189}," complete",[179,212,213],{"class":189}," access",[179,215,216],{"class":189}," to",[179,218,196],{"class":189},[179,220,221],{"class":189}," account.\n",[179,223,225,228,231,234,237,239,241,244,247,250,252,255,258,261,264],{"class":181,"line":224},2,[179,226,227],{"class":185},"For",[179,229,230],{"class":189}," better",[179,232,233],{"class":189}," security,",[179,235,236],{"class":189}," log",[179,238,190],{"class":189},[179,240,193],{"class":189},[179,242,243],{"class":189}," a",[179,245,246],{"class":189}," limited-privilege",[179,248,249],{"class":189}," personal",[179,251,213],{"class":189},[179,253,254],{"class":189}," token.",[179,256,257],{"class":189}," Learn",[179,259,260],{"class":189}," more",[179,262,263],{"class":189}," at",[179,265,266],{"class":189}," https:\u002F\u002Fdocs.docker.com\u002Fgo\u002Faccess-tokens\u002F\n",[17,268,269],{},"That means you're logged in.",[144,271,273],{"id":272},"logging-out","Logging out",[17,275,276,277,279],{},"You rarely need this — only really useful when you're on a machine that isn't yours. Run ",[95,278,107],{},":",[170,281,283],{"className":172,"code":282,"language":174,"meta":175,"style":175},"Removing login credentials for https:\u002F\u002Findex.docker.io\u002Fv1\u002F\n",[95,284,285],{"__ignoreMap":175},[179,286,287,290,293,296,299],{"class":181,"line":182},[179,288,289],{"class":185},"Removing",[179,291,292],{"class":189}," login",[179,294,295],{"class":189}," credentials",[179,297,298],{"class":189}," for",[179,300,301],{"class":189}," https:\u002F\u002Findex.docker.io\u002Fv1\u002F\n",[17,303,304],{},"That means the stored login credentials have been removed.",[144,306,308],{"id":307},"searching-docker-images","Searching Docker Images",[17,310,311,313],{},[95,312,117],{}," is dead simple — append the name of the Image you want. For example, searching for Node.js:",[170,315,317],{"className":172,"code":316,"language":174,"meta":175,"style":175},"docker search node\n",[95,318,319],{"__ignoreMap":175},[179,320,321,324,327],{"class":181,"line":182},[179,322,323],{"class":185},"docker",[179,325,326],{"class":189}," search",[179,328,329],{"class":189}," node\n",[17,331,332],{},"You'll see a long list of Node-related Images.",[17,334,335],{},[73,336],{"alt":337,"src":338},"Image list","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E4%B8%80%E6%AD%A5%E6%AD%A5%E6%8E%8C%E6%8F%A1%E5%9F%BA%E7%A4%8E-Docker\u002FdKwSAkz.png",[144,340,342],{"id":341},"pulling-a-docker-image","Pulling a Docker Image",[17,344,345],{},"Say you want to pull the Node.js Image you just searched. Run:",[170,347,349],{"className":172,"code":348,"language":174,"meta":175,"style":175},"docker pull node\n",[95,350,351],{"__ignoreMap":175},[179,352,353,355,358],{"class":181,"line":182},[179,354,323],{"class":185},[179,356,357],{"class":189}," pull",[179,359,329],{"class":189},[17,361,362],{},"You'll see:",[17,364,365],{},[73,366],{"alt":127,"src":367},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E4%B8%80%E6%AD%A5%E6%AD%A5%E6%8E%8C%E6%8F%A1%E5%9F%BA%E7%A4%8E-Docker\u002FEIFxRdN.png",[17,369,370],{},"This takes a moment. When you see:",[170,372,374],{"className":172,"code":373,"language":174,"meta":175,"style":175},"Status: Downloaded newer image for node:latest\ndocker.io\u002Flibrary\u002Fnode:latest\n",[95,375,376,395],{"__ignoreMap":175},[179,377,378,381,384,387,390,392],{"class":181,"line":182},[179,379,380],{"class":185},"Status:",[179,382,383],{"class":189}," Downloaded",[179,385,386],{"class":189}," newer",[179,388,389],{"class":189}," image",[179,391,298],{"class":189},[179,393,394],{"class":189}," node:latest\n",[179,396,397],{"class":181,"line":224},[179,398,399],{"class":185},"docker.io\u002Flibrary\u002Fnode:latest\n",[17,401,402],{},"It means the Node.js Image is now on your machine.",[17,404,405],{},"How do you actually use it? We'll get to that in a later post.",[144,407,409],{"id":408},"pushing-a-docker-image","Pushing a Docker Image",[17,411,412,414],{},[95,413,137],{}," is comparatively simple — it pushes an Image you've built to Docker Hub. We'll cover this in detail later; for now just know the command exists.",[17,416,417],{},"That's the basic Docker Hub command set.",[419,420,421],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .smYoP, html code.shiki .smYoP{--shiki-light:#6F42C1;--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .sWayO, html code.shiki .sWayO{--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#ADDCFF}html .light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html.light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: va